MSS 
=====



MSS stands for maximum segment size, it is the maximum tcp payload that can be transferred in a packet. if we need to send 10KB file, and if the MSS is 1000bytes, then it will be sent in 10 packets. MSS is negotiated in 3 way handshake. (generally 1460bytes).

]]></content>
